Idibia Gabriel, Kaduna Five of the kidnapped students of Federal College of Forestry Mechanization Afaka have been reportedly recovered, the Kaduna state security update of 5th April 2021, has revealed. A statement by the state internal security and Home Affairs commissioner Mr. Samuel Aruwan stressed that the recovered students are currently undergoing a thorough medical check-up at a military facility.“The Nigerian military has informed the Kaduna State Government that five of the many kidnapped students of the Afaka, Kaduna were recovered Monday afternoon and are presently in a military facility where they are undergoing a thorough medical check-up”, it stated. Silence on the remaining 34 students, Aruwan statement however informed that “The Kaduna State Government will provide updates on further operational feedback to be received on this case.